name: tetraacyldisaccharide 4'-kinase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: Involved with EC 2.3.1.129 (acyl-[acyl-carrier- protein]---UDP-N-acetylglucosamine O-acyltransferase) and EC 2.4.1.182 (lipid-A-disaccharide synthase) in the biosynthesis of the phosphorylated glycolipid, lipid A, in the outer membrane of Escherichia coli.

references.title: The biosynthesis of gram-negative endotoxin. A novel kinase in Escherichia coli membranes that incorporates the 4'-phosphate of lipid A.
